age_metrics.html" id="license_usage_metrics-d62e983-link">License usage metrics</a><span class="wh-tooltip"><p xmlns:toc="http://www.oxygenxml.com/ns/webhelp/toc" xmlns:xhtml="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" class="shortdesc">Using the IBM License Metric Tool, you can generate license consumption reports that         count IBM StoredIQ license usage. IBM StoredIQ is licensed by Resource Value Unit (RVU). RVU         calculation is based on terabytes IBM StoredIQ.</p></span></span></span></li><li role="treeitem" aria-expanded="false"><span data-tocid="security-d62e1005" class="topicref" data-id="security" data-state="not-ready"><span role="button" tabindex="0" aria-labelledby="button-expand-action security-d62e1005-link" class="wh-expand-btn"></span><span class="title"><a href="../Concept/security.html" id="security-d62e1005-link">Security</a><span class="wh-tooltip"><p xmlns:toc="http://www.oxygenxml.com/ns/webhelp/toc" xmlns:xhtml="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" class="shortdesc">Plan and implement specific security measures to protect the application and the data         it manages, especially when you deploy IBM StoredIQ into sensitive environments. IBM         StoredIQ keeps your data secure through encryption, security hardening, and         auditing</p></span></span></span></li></ul></li></ul>